# motoquencer: grabbing/moving a fader (a Rack mouse drag — `hold`) must NOT
# press the step's touch plate. The plate below the fader is a separate sensor;
# only a plate press (`touch`) toggles the step's gate in buttonmode 0.
#
# Regression for UAT F8: in the MFPS ratchet menu (fadermode 5, buttonmode 0) a
# mouse drag of the RATC fader toggled the step's gate off — the drag-touch was
# fed into the plate surface, so "max ratchets" appeared to silence the track.
# Here: drag step 1's fader to 1.0 (ratchets = 8) while holding it. The gate
# must still fire (default gate on), now subdivided into ratchets.
tickrate 100
patch <<<
[m4]
[motoquencer]
    clock     = I1
    fadermode = I2
    numsteps  = 2
    gate      = O2
>>>
@1 set I2 5
# drag (hold + move), as the Rack widget does — NOT a plate touch.
@2 hold F2 1
@3 move F2 1.0
@4 hold F2 0
@5 set I2 0
# period-4 clock; step0 on the 1st edge (period unknown), step1 on the 2nd.
@8 set I1 1
@9 set I1 0
@12 set I1 1
# step1 plays with 8 ratchets over its 4-tick cycle (interval 0.5 tick, each
# subgate capped below the next boundary): the gate is HIGH at the step start.
# If the drag had toggled the gate off (the F8 bug), O2 would be 0 here.
@12 expect O2 1 tol 1e-4
@13 set I1 0
# a plate touch DOES toggle the gate off (buttonmode 0 still the default).
@14 touch F2 1
@15 touch F2 0
# tick16 wraps to step 0 (still gated, default on) ...
@16 set I1 1
@17 set I1 0
# ... and tick20 is step 1 again: now silenced by the plate toggle.
@20 set I1 1
@20 expect O2 0 tol 1e-4
